          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-02-04 22:33:01" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(a figurative extension of meaning of {L:βασιλεύω&lt;SDBG:βασιλεύω:000000&gt;}[a] ‘to rule, to reign as a king,’ {D:37.64}) to be in control in an absolute manner</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to reign</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to control completely</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In a number of languages, however, it may be impossible to personify death as being capable of ‘reigning’ or ‘ruling.’ Sometimes the equivalent meaning may be expressed as ‘from the time of Adam to that of Moses there was no way for people to escape death’ or ‘… to die was certain’ ({S:04500501400004}).</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
